        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 7:53AM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 752 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lake Lawtonka, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lawton, Cache, Medicine Park, Fort Sill, Meers, Lake Lawtonka,
Wichita Mountains Wildlife Refuge, Mount Scott, Doris Campground, and
The Visitor Center.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
